  "prompt": "What are some kind words to say to a friend with a sick parent?",
  "response": "Here are some compassionate things you could say:\n\n1. \"I'm here for you if you need anything.\"\n\n2. \"I'm so sorry you're going through this.\"\n\n3. \"Please let me know how I can help.\"\n\n4. \"You're in my thoughts and prayers.\"\n\n5. \"I'm sending you strength and love.\"\n\n6. \"Would you like to talk about it?\"\n\n7. \"Take all the time you need.\"\n\n8. \"It's okay to not be okay right now.\"\n\n9. \"I'm always available if you want to chat or need support.\"\n\n10. \"Your parent is lucky to have you.\"\n\n11. \"I know this is really hard, and I'm here to listen.\"\n\n12. \"You don't have to go through this alone.\"\n\nRemember that sometimes just being present and listening is the most important thing you can do. Avoid saying things like \"Everything happens for a reason\" or \"They'll be fine,\" as these can minimize their feelings.",
